items.body:
`_foldSignatureHeader` was producing malformed wire (`v=1
	a=rsa-sha256;
	...` — missing `;` after the first segment). RFC 6376 §3.2 requires `;` to stay on the prior line at fold boundaries. The corrected output is `v=1;
	a=rsa-sha256;
	...`. Pre-v1, no compat shims — operators rotate keys / rebuild any saved signatures.
